{
  "stem": "7458.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "How in the world by mother managed to raise eight children and keep them all fed and clothed-- to this day I cannot understand it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Somehow, she must have worked 50 hours a day in order to accomplish all of that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The town itself consisted of a major square.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There were two squares, actually.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was the center of town, where the Polish church was located, surrounded by a high stone wall which plays a part in my story.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And our school, the Hebrew school, was located in that square.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Some of the shops, bakery shops, grocery stores, such as they were, were located in that square.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then there were some houses.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "People lived in various parts of the square.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Then there was a second square backing up to the large square, where there were at least two and probably several small additional synagogues.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There was the big synagogue, which was a stone structure.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "There was a wooden synagogue next to it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then there were a number of homes where there were small temples where people would pray.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They would divide up based on trades.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "For instance, shoemakers would have their own praying shtiebel they called it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Tailors would have their own shtiebel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And so life really revolved to a large extent around this square and around the religious aspects of town.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We also had a small library.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I'll never forget my brother Meyer, who was the third of the oldest siblings, after Baile and Feitche, used to carry me on his shoulders-- I remember that very clearly-- to the library, where he would read books to me when I was too little to read myself, where eventually he introduced me to books.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
